  "prompt": "Are there legal frameworks in place to combat money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several legal frameworks in place to combat money laundering:\n\n1. International Frameworks:\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- United Nations Convention Against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n\n2. National Legislation:\n- Bank Secrecy Act (USA)\n- Anti-Money Laundering (AML) regulations\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) requirements\n- Suspicious Activity Report (SAR) protocols\n\n3. Key Prevention Strategies:\n- Customer due diligence\n- Transaction monitoring\n- Reporting suspicious financial activities\n- Enhanced background checks\n- Record-keeping requirements\n\n4. Enforcement Mechanisms:\n- Regulatory investigations\n- Criminal prosecutions\n- Significant financial penalties\n- Asset seizure\n- International cooperation between law enforcement agencies\n\n5. Specific Sectors Covered:\n- Banking\n- Financial institutions\n- Real estate\n- Cryptocurrency exchanges\n- Gambling industries\n\nThese frameworks aim to detect, prevent, and prosecute money laundering activities through comprehensive legal and regulatory approaches.",
